reviews.review_text: Grateful sound! I just want to thank all who keep this phenomenal music alive and out there. Sound quality, performance quality and set lists don't mean much to me. I love a good sb but the energy of an audience recording can be very satisfying too. It's been more than 40 years since a very special friend asked if I knew the Grateful Dead. We sat on the floor and she played American Beauty for me. She sang along with Jerry on Friend of the Devil "...first one says she's got my child but it don't look like me..." ending in a smile that I will remember always. That was the day I got on the bus. Thanks Debra!
